In his State of the Union address, President Donald Trump highlighted the progress his administration has made over the past year. He spoke about the accomplishments in job creation, wage growth, and the stock market. He also discussed the passing of the biggest tax cuts in American history, the need for immigration reform, and the fight against terrorism. The president emphasized the importance of unity and working together to achieve the goals of the American people. He also recognized individuals who have shown bravery and heroism in the face of adversity. The president called on Congress to pass legislation that would address issues such as infrastructure, healthcare, and immigration. He ended his speech by expressing his belief in the American people and the greatness of the country.